column168: DURING PRE-TRIP INSPECTION DRIVER NOTICED A SMALL LEAK AT THE REAR SIDE OF THE TANKER. A RUBBER PATCH WAS INSTALLED OVER THE LEAK WITH BINDERS AND ABS ORBANT MATERIAL WAS PLACED AROUND THE AREA SO AS TO CONTAIN LEAKING MATERIA L. MATERIAL WAS THEN TRANSFERRED TO ANOTHER TANKER FOR DELIVERY. AFTER FURTHER INSPECTION, IT APPEARS THAT THE INNER TUBBER LINING HAD RUPTU RED, LETTING THE ACID ESCAPE TO THE INNER WALL OF THE TANKER, WHICH INTURN CAUSED THE LEAK. SPILL WAS CONTAINED WITH THE USE OF VARIOUS ABSORBANT MATERIALS AND PUT INT O A CONTAINER FOR DISPOSAL. AREA WAS THEN DECONTAMINATED WITH A CAUSTIC SOL UTION, WHICH INTURN WAS REMOVED WITH THE USE OF A VACUUM AND PUT INTO A CON TAINER FOR DISPOSAL.
